      <pdf>j074.pdf</pdf>
      <abstract>Let {Q&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, Q&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;, Q&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;,...}
be chain recurrent set components of a
dynamical system. A connection Q&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#8594;Q&lt;sub&gt;j&lt;/sub&gt;
is said to exist if there is a point x such that &amp;#945; -
limit set of x is in Q&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; and 
&amp;#969; - limit set of x is in Q&lt;sub&gt;j&lt;/sub&gt;.

Let the matrix S=(s&lt;sub&gt;ij&lt;/sub&gt;) be such that s&lt;sub&gt;ij&lt;/sub&gt;=1
if there is the connection Q&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#8594;Q&lt;sub&gt;j&lt;/sub&gt;,
s&lt;sub&gt;ii&lt;/sub&gt;=1 and s&lt;sub&gt;ij&lt;/sub&gt;=0 in other
case. The matrix S is named the structure matrix of dynamical system
f. By the definition, the structure matrix is a topological invariant. The
main result:

If the dynamical system has a finite number of chain recurrent components
with the stable connections then there exist a finite algorithm for
construction of the structure matrix.</abstract>
      <title>The Structure Matrix of Dynamical System</title>
    </articleInfo>
